<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-26-0457 </DOCNO><TEXT>The long-term global demand of energy, it is to be assumed, will be decisivelydetermined by the quantitative development of the world population. Alldemographic studies indicate a strong (exponential) growth of the worldpopulation particularly still in this century and in Third World countries.This will result in a high global demand of primary energy, to be metonly by shifting from fossil fuels to other fuels (also because of therelease of CO/sub 2/) and by extending the contribution of nuclear andsolar energy.</TEXT></DOC>